name: controller-rules
description: Rails Controller Standards
glob: app/controllers/**/*.rb

---
When working with controllers:

1. Controller Organization
- Keep controllers focused and minimal
- Use concerns for shared functionality
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Use proper namespacing

2. Actions
- Keep actions simple and focused
- Use before_action for common setup
- Use strong parameters
- Return appropriate status codes
- Handle errors gracefully

3. Response Formats
- Focus on HTML responses
- No JSON unless specifically needed
- Use Turbo Streams for dynamic updates
- Use proper content types

4. Security
- Use proper authentication
- Use authorization (if needed)
- Protect from forgery
- Validate parameters
- Prevent mass assignment
- Use secure headers

5. Performance
- Keep queries minimal
- Use eager loading
- Cache when appropriate
- Use Russian Doll caching
- Monitor N+1 queries

6. Testing
- Test all actions
- Test edge cases
- Test authentication
- Test authorization
- Test error conditions 